{"name":"Faerie Speech","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Many faeries have a Pretense called Faerie Speech, which they use instead of acquiring human languages. Faeries seem to know the same languages as whomever they are talking to. If speaking to a group that has demonstrated mixed linguistic skills, the faerie may select which language to speak in.</span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This effect occurs whenever the faerie speaks and costs no Might. It is not magically resisted, because the effect only alters the behavior of the faerie. If the faerie has not heard a person from its audience speak, it may only use whichever language it last used with humans. Once its audience speaks, the faerie may then converse in the correct language for its audience.</span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">In the bestiary chapter, Faerie Speech is frequently given to characters designed as NPCs. Characters designed for possible use by players have this Virtue more rarely, to free up a Virtue slot, but it is still appropriate for a wide variety of faeries.</span></p>","source":"RoP:F","page":50,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"faerie-speech","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.9","createdTime":1732293625851,"modifiedTime":1743830551217,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey","exportSource":null},"folder":"XwOh5akgyjxNE2dG","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3,"wUH1ww0o0zQEBtKr":3},"_id":"9te6C1H9ihySHLb6","sort":700000}
{"name":"Troupe Upbringing","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You were raised among a group of entertainers, spending much of your childhood traveling from town to town. Rolls involving Abilities in a selected area (which you should have approved by the storyguide) receive a +2 modifier. Examples might include tumbling and acrobatics, knife throwing and juggling, or storytelling and acting.</p><p> </p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"troupe-upbringing","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729316634167,"modifiedTime":1731255711120,"lastModifiedBy":"tBE5EmoIXLzf3maM","exportSource":null},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"9vt8UaeytpS9Sk5m","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Personal Vis Source","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have exclusive access to a supply of raw vis. Determine the amount and type with the help of your troupe; the yield should be about one tenth as much as the player covenant expects to gather per year at the beginning of the saga. The yield of your source does not normally change over the course of time, even if the covenant uncovers new sources.</p><p> </p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"personal-vis-source","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729316634167,"modifiedTime":1731255711120,"lastModifiedBy":"tBE5EmoIXLzf3maM","exportSource":null},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"9xVHRzNknDyxGfWu","sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Master of (Form) Creatures","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The character can tame animals and other unintelligent beings whose Magic Might is aligned with a particular Form. During character creation, the character may take Magic Lore, and this Virtue may be taken multiple times, once for each Form.</p><p> See page @@ for rules for training magical (and mundane) animals.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"master-of-form-creatures","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729670882205,"modifiedTime":1743830551217,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey","exportSource":null},"folder":"XwOh5akgyjxNE2dG","_id":"A6IPUya5UaKnXpdc","sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Minor Rune Focus","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The vitki has a magical focus with a single rune used in a particular type of rune magic (see the Vitkar Magic Foci sidebar). Whenever the vitki casts a rune spell with an effect appropriate to the focus and the chosen rune, and inscribes this rune into the material associated with the focus, you may double the vitki’s score in the rune used for the formula.</span></p>","source":"HMRE","page":121,"indexKey":"minor-rune-focus","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","credits":"","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"qCYCMZYUJz0toJkP","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.16","createdTime":1757739862726,"modifiedTime":1757739862726,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J","exportSource":null},"_id":"A7s88MKrTbbLuPXk","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Falconer","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The character trains hawks and falcons for a noble patron, and is responsible for the training, breeding, and health of the animals. He often has a personal servant to assist, and is an important member of the noble household, treated with great respect. He should possess the Ability Profession : <span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, 'Times New Roman_EmbeddedFont', 'Times New Roman_MSFontService', serif\">Falconer</span>, which governs the care of the birds, treatment of their diseases, and acquisition and breeding of hawks and falcons. The Ability Animal Handling is used for the training of the hawks. A specialist in non-falcons, such as the hawks, is called an austringer. </p><p> A <span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, 'Times New Roman_EmbeddedFont', 'Times New Roman_MSFontService', serif\">falconer </span>receives 50 extra experience points at character generation to spend on the Abilities Animal Handling, Area Lore, Etiquette, Hunt, Latin, Profession: <span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, 'Times New Roman_EmbeddedFont', 'Times New Roman_MSFontService', serif\">Falconer</span>, and Ride. Many <span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, 'Times New Roman_EmbeddedFont', 'Times New Roman_MSFontService', serif\">falconer</span>s are also Educated. </p><p>Also permitted in Eastern Christendom </p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"socialWestern","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"falconer","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729488571763,"modifiedTime":1731255711120,"lastModifiedBy":"tBE5EmoIXLzf3maM","exportSource":null},"folder":"Dlca5muDKIfBSi6F","_id":"A93kgNT7FBRMtADm","sort":3400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Archieunuch","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have risen to enjoy the status and privilege associated with the most important and talented eunuchs, the <span style=\"font-family: Times, 'Times_EmbeddedFont', 'Times_MSFontService', Times New Roman, serif\">archieunuch</span>s. Although you are not a ruler in your own right, a ruler likely depends on you to govern effectively and has thus granted you considerable authority to act in his stead. Due to this status and importance, you wield significant influence among the lesser nobility. You might serve either as a regional administrator, an important courtier, or a general, and there are numerous servants and possibly other subordinate eunuchs under your command. You have been granted a residence, either within a castle or palace, or elsewhere. Due to your education, you may take Academic Abilities during character creation. This social status is found in the eastern Roman empire, with its capital at Constantinople, and does not exist in western Europe or much of the Muslim world. This Virtue is only available to male characters, who must also be eunuchs.</p><p> </p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"socialEastern","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"archieunuch","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729343443389,"modifiedTime":1731255711120,"lastModifiedBy":"tBE5EmoIXLzf3maM","exportSource":null},"folder":"5doiTaY9KQf8IBzO","_id":"AFPa5I5XtPf521Qs","sort":1200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
