{"name":"Short-Lived Runes","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The magic in the vitki’s runes naturally fades, and unlike other rune spells is not permanent as long as the rune is not damaged. The storyguide should secretly roll a stress die (no botch) on the Nátt-thel Duration Chart to determine how long any given effect lasts.</span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The vitki can spend Confidence or vis to lengthen the duration, as well as to increase his casting total. The storyguide should add 1 to this duration roll for each pawn or Point spent for this purpose during the casting.</span></p>","source":"HMRE","page":123,"indexKey":"natt-thel-prone","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"credits":""},"effects":[],"folder":"8vR2Wj34GP8nOK1V","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.16","createdTime":1757739862726,"modifiedTime":1757739862726,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J","exportSource":null},"_id":"JUQZHoW3hDTVRVNp","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Poorly Trained Gruagach","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Due to the incompetence or negligence of the gruagach’s master, the character must spend 50 fewer experience points on gruagach Arts and take 25 fewer levels of spells than normal. This Flaw may be taken multiple times, but may not reduce the gained experience to 0.</span></p>","source":"HMRE","page":57,"indexKey":"poorly-trained-gruagach","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"credits":""},"effects":[],"folder":"AxenlsqwBJaySCAv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.16","createdTime":1757739626053,"modifiedTime":1757739626053,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J","exportSource":null},"_id":"JV2GwEt8hM46MgYD","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Educated (Bardic)","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The character has attended one of the great bardic schools in Hibernia, either to receive an education (in which case he need not have attempted the punishing examination) or to commence training as a bard (in which case you should also take an appropriate bardic Social Status Virtue). For Senior or Master Bards this Virtue represents additional years of study. You receive 50 extra experience points to spend on Art of Memory, Profession: Storyteller, Profession: Poet, any Area Lore, or any Organization Lore.</p><p> </p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"educated-bardic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729451788830,"modifiedTime":1731255711129,"lastModifiedBy":"tBE5EmoIXLzf3maM","exportSource":null},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"JgnFYsN8G8lTLSc5","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
