{"name":"Gruagach","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The character is a member of the gruagach magical tradition. The character may perform gruagach laboratory activities and is a member of a gruagach collective. This Virtue is compatible  with many other Social Virtues and Flaws, and with Wealthy and Poor. A normal gruagach must spend time supporting himself. UnGifted gruagachan usually do this by performing their normal vocations, but more-powerful Gifted gruagachan may perform services for the community, provide services to local lords, or receive rewards for enforcing justice — these services are usually arranged for by unGifted gruagachan, who interact with the general populace.</span></p>","source":"HMRE","page":56,"indexKey":"gruagach","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","credits":"","type":"social","impact":{"value":"free"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"ZFzMK6RgEkGopaas","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.16","createdTime":1757739626053,"modifiedTime":1757739626053,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J","exportSource":null},"_id":"PXVINNjEbtWbd1HU","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Guild Dean","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The character is the ultimate authority of his guild, the man who decides many of the important decisions that face the guild and represents it politically. The character is involved in town politics, long-term trade contacts, and negotiations with other guilds and local craftsmen. The town’s population views him as an important and prestigious member of their community. You may select Academic Abilities at character generation.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":40,"type":"socialWestern","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"guild-dean","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729512579520,"modifiedTime":1731255711137,"lastModifiedBy":"tBE5EmoIXLzf3maM","exportSource":null},"folder":"5doiTaY9KQf8IBzO","_id":"Ph8g59Vdrzjak2KE","sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Transformation Prone","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The character is especially prone to undergoing transformation, the gruagach equivalent of Twilight. The player must roll</span> <span class=\"fontstyle0\">to resist transformation on a single magical botch, rather than on a double botch like most gruagachan.</span></p>","source":"HMRE","page":57,"indexKey":"transformation-prone","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"credits":""},"effects":[],"folder":"AxenlsqwBJaySCAv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.16","createdTime":1757739626053,"modifiedTime":1757739626053,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J","exportSource":null},"_id":"Pj3GiGn2i5ZKsLhL","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"MewGclJOm3EmdeRI","name":"Survive Without Water","type":"quality","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The creature can survive without water for up to two weeks.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"survive-without-water","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"mundane","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"wUH1ww0o0zQEBtKr":3},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.11","createdTime":1733252238645,"modifiedTime":1733252750707,"lastModifiedBy":"wUH1ww0o0zQEBtKr","exportSource":null},"_id":"Ptz6SP4XzykW3frY","sort":100000}
{"name":"Almogavar","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The character is a member of a band of mercenaries and raiders, living a life of adventure according to a code of honor and discipline. He shares a bond of solidarity with his fellows, and they can depend on each other’s loyalty. He has Standard Armaments, and may take Martial Abilities. He may choose to be the Adalil, the second-in-command, at no additional cost, getting an increase in both authority and responsibility. He is supported by his unit, and may not take the Poor Flaw or Wealthy Virtue.</p><p> </p><p>These characters are from the Iberian Peninsula, and if they are particularly far from home the troupe may rule that this is not available as a social status.</p><p> </p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"almogavar","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729336168698,"modifiedTime":1731255711137,"lastModifiedBy":"tBE5EmoIXLzf3maM","exportSource":null},"folder":"Dlca5muDKIfBSi6F","_id":"PupiTXgIArIWzjPC","sort":4100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Merchant Adventurer","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The character is in command of a ship, and a crew. The character has sufficient capital for a cargo, but may have substantial debts, which may be represented by the Favors Flaw. See </p><p><em>City and Guild</em> for more details on trade. A merchant adventurer who owns a share of the company he works for should select the Partner Virtue instead of this one.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"merchant-adventurer","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729672015565,"modifiedTime":1731255711137,"lastModifiedBy":"tBE5EmoIXLzf3maM","exportSource":null},"folder":"Dlca5muDKIfBSi6F","_id":"Py4R1uuWpKnz59FW","sort":2800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Hermetic Experience","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The character has experience with the magi of the Order of Hermes. Maybe he is currently employed by a covenant, once served in the retinue of a magus, or has had other dealings or disputes with them. In any case, you have an additional 50 experience points to spend on Order of Hermes Lore, Magic Lore, or Latin. You cannot spend other experience points on Magic Lore or Latin unless the character has another Virtue or Flaw permitting this. This Virtue may be taken by any grog or </p><p>covenfolk, or those who have had an exceptionally close relationship with the Order of Hermes. It <em>may</em> be taken by a magus, but there is usually no point.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"hermetic-experience","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729512778539,"modifiedTime":1731255711137,"lastModifiedBy":"tBE5EmoIXLzf3maM","exportSource":null},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"QCnvZ3e7BB4c6Oiv","sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Strong Amulet Magic","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The character is especially adept at creating chartae and amulets. When creating either, the character receives a +10 bonus to all Lab Totals.</span></p>","source":"HMRE","page":82,"indexKey":"strong-amulet-magic","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","credits":"","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"a5lJqnaWGoCK0Bb9","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.16","createdTime":1757739788320,"modifiedTime":1757739788320,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J","exportSource":null},"_id":"QI1pmZNkIehN26I8","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Clan Ilfetu","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The character is a member of Clan Ilfetu within House Bjornaer, and has received extra training in the rituals of the House. You receive 50 extra experience points that may be spent on House Bjornaer Lore, Magic Lore (with a specialty in the Great Beasts), and Gothic, the dead language that the House uses for all of its rituals. It is possible that the magus has also been Initiated into the Esoteric Mystery of Divination and Augury (see <em>The Mysteries Revised Edition,</em> page 58); if so, that Virtue must be purchased with the normal allowance of ten points of Virtues and Flaws. Clan Ilfetu teaches the Divination method of haemagmomancy, which is divination by observing the blood splatters of wounded animals; this gives the following bonuses to Divination: +5 family, +3 Corpus. See <em>Houses of Hermes: Mystery Cults,</em> page 12, for more details on House Bjornaer and the role of Clan Ilfetu.</p><p> </p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"clan-ilfetu","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729366295155,"modifiedTime":1731255711138,"lastModifiedBy":"tBE5EmoIXLzf3maM","exportSource":null},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"QmVYkoV1mBNqaN0d","sort":2500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Sharp Ears","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You hear better than most. You get a +3 bonus to all rolls in</p><p>volving hearing.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"sharp-ears","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729316634167,"modifiedTime":1731255711138,"lastModifiedBy":"tBE5EmoIXLzf3maM","exportSource":null},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"QrNvOMnaEW5sYNOQ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Senior Bard","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The character has spent fi</p><p>ve or six years at a bardic school, and is ranked a <em>Cano </em>or <em>Cli </em>respectively. The character has a Local Reputation of 2 representing his fame as a storyteller.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The character has a minimum age of 22, and you can spend experience points on any Realm Lore at character creation even if otherwise unable to take Arcane Abilities. The character should have at least one Area Lore, Realm Lore, or Organization Lore at a score of 5, and has an extra 90 experience points to spend on Art of Memory, Profession: Storyteller, Profession: Poet, any Area Lore, any Organization Lore, Faerie Lore, or Magic Lore. This Social Status is only available in Hibernia.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"socialHibernia","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"senior-bard","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729769546933,"modifiedTime":1731255711138,"lastModifiedBy":"tBE5EmoIXLzf3maM","exportSource":null},"folder":"Dlca5muDKIfBSi6F","_id":"QsdCkjjhCdW0f261","sort":1000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Gender Shift","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Each midnight, the character may choose to change genders. The character’s male and female forms are consistent across transformations, and usually appear to be blood kin of each other. The character’s Personality Traits may vary slightly between forms. Pregnant characters may not use this ability.</p><p> </p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"gender-shift","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":true},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729510151538,"modifiedTime":1743830551217,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey","exportSource":null},"folder":"XwOh5akgyjxNE2dG","_id":"QyCvon8OxBo7GOTp","sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
