{"name":"Piercing Gaze","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>By staring intently at people you make them feel uneasy, as if you are peering into their souls. Those with ulterior motives, uneasy consciences, or lying tongues must make rolls against an appropriate Personality Trait, Guile, or whatever the storyguide deems appropriate, to remain calm. Furthermore, you gain a +3 to rolls involving intimidation. Faeries and demons are unfazed by your power.</p><p> </p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"piercing-gaze","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729316634167,"modifiedTime":1731255711145,"lastModifiedBy":"tBE5EmoIXLzf3maM","exportSource":null},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"XTGU8VfDOzW1914b","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
